<br>
Since the dawn of our race elven mithril smithing has served our folk in shaping the world of Norrath.  My father, Naythox, learned the secrets from the All Mother, secrets which enable our spell casters to wear mettalic armor and manipulate the arcane forces like no other beings.<br>
<br>
With the fall of Takish-Hiz and the rapid erosion of the Elddar Forest into what are today called "Befallen" and the "Ro Desert", much of our lore in this art was lost.  I was but an apprentice mithril smith when the Prince of Hate stole away the first king and queen, and faced little opportunity to master this craft in years past.  <br>
<br>
Today, thanks to the work of many fellow elves who recovered lost writings and discovered a new vein of mithril, I have advanced my skill in forging mithril based armor.  I offer this service to you, Illuvitae, to any of you willing to help gather the rare materials this armor can be yours.  <br>
<br>
If you wish to acquire this superb armor, or learn this trade, you may find a tome on Mithril Smithing at dalkingdom.freeservers.com  Reading this guide will open your eyes to what helped make our ancestors the dominant force on the continent of Tunaria.  <br>
<br>
Outfitting yourselves in this armor of our race will further distinguish yourselves as the Fayguard.<br>
<br>
May the All Mother guide and protect you always,<br>
<br>
Tearis Thex<br>
King of the Dal<br>
dalkingdom.freeservers.com <p>Tearis Thex
