We are the Chosen Ones, let nothing stand in our way."</i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub45.ezboard.com/uvalindel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Valindel</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_star.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#660000>(2/21/01 3:40:25 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Components</span><hr size=1> Well Blue Diamonds aren't worth near 8k on blue servers, more like 2-3 from what it looks like.  And they used to be worth about 4-500pp before they BD jewelry patch.  VI sometimes has their head up their arse. <p>Valendil, Illuvitae<br>
High Elf Cleric of Tunare</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#99CC66><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub45.ezboard.com/utearis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tearis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#660000>(2/21/01 4:12:24 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Components</span><hr size=1> An imbued elven chain tunic requires three enchanted large bricks of mithril and an gem imbued by a cleric (and in some cases a wizard depending on your religion).  This translates into 3 blue diamonds per attempt for a tunic.  <br>
<br>
Other race armor gems are similar in difficulty, but not as costly.  Many feedback reports have been sent in about this, I urge you all to add your voices to this.  Today's patch doesn't list this as fixed.  If you submit a feedback, here are two solutions we've been suggesting:<br>
<br>
1.  Make blue diamonds available from elven vendors (240pp when bought from one before they became a hot item).  I doubt this solution will fly as then everyone would have the velium jewelry.<br>
<br>
2.  Change the type of gem required to a more common one than a blue diamond.  (this is the preferred solution)<br>
<br>
In the meantime, other race armors are available and I will put aside all other business to craft some for you, at cost (special discount to Illuvitae).<br>
<br>
Here's all you have to do -<br>
1.  Moonlight Temper.  We have a brewer skilled enough to succeed in making this difficult brew needed for all elven armor.  This requires three ingredients, a) Essence of Moonlight (found on will sappers in Mistmoore), b) vial of swirling mist (found on mist/steam elementals outside the Mino caves in Steamfont), c) morning dew (spawns on the ground in Lesser Fay and Greater Fay in specific location between 5am-8am) - ask Avathor for specific locations to gather morning dew. <br>
<br>
Give the morning dew to Keradim, our brewer, or myself.<br>
<br>
2.  I'll take you to the vendor in Felwithe to buy large bricks of Mithril ore for the pieces you want made and also the vendor who sells patterns and molds for the armor for you to buy.  The highest cost for a piece of &quot;normal&quot; elven chain is 100pp, and for koada'dal mithril plate's largest piece costs 200pp per attempt.  Note:  these are the highest costs per piece.<br>
<br>
3.  Once I have the Moonlight Temper, molds and ore, I have sufficient supplies of the remaining ingredients to use the Koada'Dal forge to attempt the armor.<br>
<br>
I've invested about 17,000pp in raising my smithing near the Grandmaster skill to make this, and would welcome the opportunity to raise the skill further helping you.  I'm not in this for profit, my payoff is seeing more elves in this armor and especially to aid &quot;pure team&quot; elves by selling it at cost.<br>
<br>
We continuously gather materials for Moonlight Temper and if I have a surplus (unlikely but possible), I will charge a nominal fee for the Moonlight Temper.<br>
<br>
Some recipes are still broken for the race armor and it appears they were not fixed today.  They will be eventually I'm certain.  One day I hope they change the requirement for blue diamonds to make the imbued armor.  In the meantime, koada'dal plate is superb armor for bards and melee classes.  Normal elven chain can be worn by casters, but has no Int, Wis, Cha, and MR bonuses.<br>
<br>
Nothing would please me more than to spend hours at the koada'dal forge outfitting the Dal Kingdom and Illuvitae with elven armor.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub45.ezboard.com/beverquest6820.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=xaeria>Xaeria</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#660000>(2/21/01 5:56:21 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Elven Armor</span><hr size=1> Now I see why this guy is king <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#99CC66><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub45.ezboard.com/udorkmid.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dorkmid</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#660000>(2/21/01 6:09:27 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Elven Armor</span><hr size=1> Its good to be the king. <p>Dorkmid 
